parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fractured Plastic Fuel Line Couplers/Quick Disconnects
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the plastic fuel line couplers/quick disconnects can cause a gasoline leak, which can lead to a fire hazard, potentially resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Gasoline leaking from the right side of the motorcycle
gasoline spraying onto the rider's leg and foot
gasoline pouring out of the right side of the bike onto the road
cracked or broken plastic fuel line couplers/quick disconnects.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS brake system can cause the brakes to lock or seize, leading to accidents, injuries, and potentially even fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden and unexpected brake lock-up
failure of the brakes to release
ABS modulator activation on normal braking
brake failure even when the brake lever is released
rear brake rotor malfunction
floating points on the rotor melting
rotor movement in all directions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake rotor can cause the ABS modulator to activate unnecessarily, leading to unpredictable braking behavior and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Floating points on the rotor melting
rotor movement in all directions
ABS modulator activation on normal braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the final drive can cause loss of power to the wheels, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or stranding the rider. This can be particularly hazardous at high speeds or in heavy traffic conditions.
symptoms: Rear wheel loose
smaller bearing race spun on shaft
crown bearing cage destroyed
loss of power to the wheels.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the front fork leg can cause the motorcycle to become unstable, leading to a loss of control and potentially resulting in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The front fork leg breaks
causing the motorcycle to stand up straight and lose control
resulting in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear wheel bearing can cause the wheel to drag, leading to a loss of control and potentially resulting in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The rear wheel makes a dragging sound
the wheel seems to be dragging on the inside of the rotor
the bearing retainer in the final drive bearing is coning out
the bearing has been obliterated and moved from its spot inside the rear hub.
